## Limitations

The findings are based on survey data, which can be influenced by the phrasing of questions and the timing of the survey. Additionally, the data reflects perceptions, which may not always align with actual tax policies or economic realities. The reports primarily focus on federal income taxes, potentially overlooking state and local tax perceptions. Furthermore, the data is limited to the United States and may not reflect global perspectives on taxation.